      <div class="msgContentFrame">As ive been leveling fishing quite a bit lately I feel like the job is more and more useless. <br /> <br />Botany and Mining most of the stuff you gather serves a purpose. <br /> <br />It seems for fishing 95% of the stuff you gather is to make sand.  <br /> <br />Then theres the occasional thing thats actually useful (ie fish glue). <br /> <br />Are there thta many useful things I can actually gather from fishing @ higher levels (rank 30-40+) that makes this job useful down the road, or am I better off quitting while im ahead and switching to a useful gathering prof ? <br /> <br /> <br />(and I know that a large part of why fishing sucks is because of how useless cooking is atm, but even alot of the cooking recipes require far more botany stuff than fishing)</div>
