      <div class="msgContentFrame">Well you can still gather coral, I'm not sure what they are used for but I heard third hand they were used for elemental damaging arrow heads.  Also agreed about the sand but, but perhaps we don't know the proper recipies. I also believe with the right clams/oysters and HQ'ing on em you can most likely get pearls instead of sand. (But that is a theory, it would make sense though, it was that way in FFXI.) <br /> <br />Also aside from glue items, corals and perhaps pearls from oysters... Mmh... Then there is blindfish for blind poison, spearfishing for for lac bugs(wood colors), bugs for various poisons for alchemy. Also found snakes that can I'm guessing be made into a venom poison?  <br /> <br />As for skills, it's never a bad plan to have skills from all gathering classes if you plan on mainly focusing on gathering. Though as far as skills go for gathering, they kinda have rather optional skills only good for rather specifik purposes that only show up once in a million years for other gathering classes. Truth of seas I think it was, was decent, gives you a 100% shard gain rate every harvest acording to your elemental stats afinity. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 17th 2010 10:36am by mjv </span></i></div>
